My code loads such bundle with RequireJS.
Define() function is defined in global namespace, and backbone decides to use AMD definition, instead of CommonJS. And because of that calling require("backbone") somewhere inside of bundled code we get empty object in return.

Many libs use exactly this UMD format, so modifying sources to fix that is not a good idea.

As a solution could be overriding most common global functions like define(), require() to undefined inside of a bundle's wrapper function, so UMD would see local define, instead of global.

